cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.CR

This paper discusses the challenges and concepts related to name-based group communication in the context of information-centric networking (ICN). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the scalability and distribution of content, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses security and privacy concerns, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper proposes a new naming concept, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
